<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="186" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,582,1183]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186">
Male: Scapes each 
<quantity box="[372,474,582,607]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.85" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" unit="mm" value="4.85">4.85 mm</quantity>
long, covered with long, dense setae, having 
<number box="[1000,1014,583,607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" value="2.0">2</number>
dorsal processes in basal fifth: basal process slender, cylindrical, and apically curved; more distal process thumb-like (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1176,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[272,1298,202,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[255,1312,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Lepidostoma lidderwatense sp. nov. 13 – 16, genitalia: 13, dorsal; 14, ventral; 15, left lateral; 16, phallic apparatus, left lateral. 17, head with maxillary and labial palps and antennal scape, right lateral. 18, right forewing, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266143/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="186">
Fig. 
<number box="[1145,1176,619,643]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palpi each 
<quantity box="[151,253,655,679]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.94" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" unit="mm" value="1.94">1.94 mm</quantity>
; 
<number box="[264,277,654,679]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" value="2.0">2</number>
-segmented, first segment longer, about as long as labial palpi, second segment one-third as long as first segment and straight (
<figureCitation box="[401,486,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[272,1298,202,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[255,1312,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Lepidostoma lidderwatense sp. nov. 13 – 16, genitalia: 13, dorsal; 14, ventral; 15, left lateral; 16, phallic apparatus, left lateral. 17, head with maxillary and labial palps and antennal scape, right lateral. 18, right forewing, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266143/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="186">
Fig. 
<number box="[455,486,691,715]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). Average length of each forewing 
<quantity box="[887,974,691,715]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" unit="mm" value="9.7">9.7 mm</quantity>
(n = 
<number box="[1037,1054,691,715]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" value="2.0">2</number>
). Wings covered with fine scales, anal groove with 
<number box="[346,360,727,751]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" value="4.0">4</number>
postcubital cells, central cell 
<number box="[693,728,726,751]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as long as distal cells (
<figureCitation box="[1054,1138,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[272,1298,202,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[255,1312,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Lepidostoma lidderwatense sp. nov. 13 – 16, genitalia: 13, dorsal; 14, ventral; 15, left lateral; 16, phallic apparatus, left lateral. 17, head with maxillary and labial palps and antennal scape, right lateral. 18, right forewing, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266143/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="186">
Fig. 
<number box="[1107,1138,727,751]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,582,1183]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186">
Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[322,464,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[272,1298,202,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[255,1312,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Lepidostoma lidderwatense sp. nov. 13 – 16, genitalia: 13, dorsal; 14, ventral; 15, left lateral; 16, phallic apparatus, left lateral. 17, head with maxillary and labial palps and antennal scape, right lateral. 18, right forewing, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266143/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="186">
Figs. 
<number box="[390,464,762,787]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" value="14.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="13.0">13–16</number>
</figureCitation>
): Segment IX apicodorsally broadly rounded, somewhat dome-shaped. Segment X divided on midline forming pair of processes, each having basal half broad with lateral margin triangular and distal half narrower, projecting as ventromesal lobe extended posteroventrad (
<figureCitation box="[979,1065,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[272,1298,202,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[255,1312,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Lepidostoma lidderwatense sp. nov. 13 – 16, genitalia: 13, dorsal; 14, ventral; 15, left lateral; 16, phallic apparatus, left lateral. 17, head with maxillary and labial palps and antennal scape, right lateral. 18, right forewing, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266143/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="186">
Fig. 
<number box="[1034,1065,835,859]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages each with basal segment subrectangular in lateral and ventral views, apical segment slender, short, finger-like, curved mesad (
<figureCitation box="[159,305,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[272,1298,202,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[255,1312,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Lepidostoma lidderwatense sp. nov. 13 – 16, genitalia: 13, dorsal; 14, ventral; 15, left lateral; 16, phallic apparatus, left lateral. 17, head with maxillary and labial palps and antennal scape, right lateral. 18, right forewing, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266143/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="186">Figs. 13, 14</figureCitation>
). Phallic apparatus dilated near base, hump-like dorsally, apical two-thirds long and cylindrical; parameres aligned with phallic apparatus, tapering to acute apices.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,837,978,1003]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" type="etymology">
