<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="186" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,582,1183]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1086,1111]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Mosely 1939" authorityName="Mosely" authorityYear="1939" box="[689,1085,1086,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidostomatidae" genus="Lepidostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nagana">
<emphasis box="[689,927,1086,1110]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="186">Lepidostoma nagana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mosely" box="[936,1085,1086,1111]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" refString="Mosely, M. E. (1939) The Indian caddis-flies (Trichoptera) VII: Sericostomatidae (Cont.), Journal of the Bombay Natural History Society, 41, 332 - 339." type="journal article" year="1939">
Mosely 
<number box="[1029,1085,1087,1111]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" value="1939.0">1939</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in that segment IX has its dorsum extended posterad and is rounded in lateral view, segment X has dorsolateral processes that are apically triangular in dorsal view, and the dorsolateral processes are broader in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1185,1321,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[272,1298,202,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[255,1312,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Lepidostoma lidderwatense sp. nov. 13 – 16, genitalia: 13, dorsal; 14, ventral; 15, left lateral; 16, phallic apparatus, left lateral. 17, head with maxillary and labial palps and antennal scape, right lateral. 18, right forewing, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266143/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="186">
Figs. 
<number box="[1248,1321,1158,1183]" pageId="5" pageNumber="186" value="14.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="13.0">13–15</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
